{
  "number": 370,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/370",
  "title": "headerFooter adds too much markup",
  "body": "Currently, all the widgets that implement the `headerFooter` decorator will generate a `<div class=\"ais-header\">` and `<div class=\"ais-footer\">` markup before and after. This occurs even if the said header and footer templates are empty.\n\nWhile implementing the ecommerce theme, I tried to replicate the default `header` style like this:\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/10763274/a15a532e-7cc9-11e5-9b8c-a7d6b36d4f95.png)\n\nThis works well for any widget that should appear in an e-commerce sidebar but does not work with other widgets like the `stats`:\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/10763294/b00abd46-7cc9-11e5-80da-01ff9da8c0ce.png)\n\nI'm not sure how to tackle that one. Maybe only adding the markup if a template for header/footer is passed as well? This would work for me, but do you see any issue in doing it that way?\n",
  "created_at": "2015-10-27T15:44:39Z",
